# MPD - GameVault

Version SQLite conforme a docs/TASKS.md et au code Hibernate actuel.

## Table games

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS games (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    developer TEXT,
    publisher TEXT,
    releaseYear INTEGER,
    platform TEXT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    rating REAL,
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'IN_COLLECTION',
    coverPath TEXT,
    addedAt TEXT,
    CHECK (releaseYear IS NULL OR releaseYear BETWEEN 1950 AND 2100),
    CHECK (rating IS NULL OR rating BETWEEN 0.0 AND 10.0),
    CHECK (status IN ('IN_COLLECTION', 'TO_PLAY', 'IN_PROGRESS', 'COMPLETED', 'ABANDONED'))
);
```

## Index utiles

```sql
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_games_title ON games(title);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_games_platform ON games(platform);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_games_developer ON games(developer);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_games_status ON games(status);
```

## Correspondance Hibernate

- `id` : `Long`, cle primaire auto-generee.
- `title` : `String`, obligatoire.
- `developer` : `String`, optionnel.
- `publisher` : `String`, optionnel.
- `releaseYear` : `Integer`, optionnel.
- `platform` : `String`, obligatoire.
- `description` : `String`, optionnel, limite applicative 2000 caracteres.
- `rating` : `Double`, optionnel.
- `status` : `GameStatus`, stocke en texte via `EnumType.STRING`.
- `coverPath` : `String`, optionnel.
- `addedAt` : `LocalDate`, stocke comme texte par SQLite/Hibernate.

## Remarque

Hibernate cree ou met a jour automatiquement la table via `hibernate.hbm2ddl.auto=update`. Le SQL ci-dessus sert de reference MPD pour documenter la structure cible de la base SQLite.
